data: {"type":"response.output_item.done","item":{"type":"a2a_preview_call_output","id":"fco_006932df935e4ec1006a15d4ab142481949ecac44b084101e3","agent_reference":{"type":"agent_reference","name":"cs-e2e-tests-client","version":"1"},"response_id":"resp_006932df935e4ec1006a15d48b6b388194ab040655578dedf9","call_id":"call_a72b315464a34732bb92b248f51e878c","name":"workiqc4k5h8","output":"You have **3 meetings scheduled for today** on your calendar. Here’s a clear breakdown to help you plan your evening:\n\n---\n\n### \uD83D\uDDD3️ Today’s Meetings\n\n#### 1. [DevEx Engineering: weekly meeting](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meeting/details?eventId=AAMkAGI4NTJlOTY2LWVhYTgtNDUwMy04MmFlLTBiOTFhY2EyYmI5NAFRAAgI3rq5ut3AAEYAAAAAxlcDfIcKC0iM2tlcAvavNgcAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QAAAAABDQAAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QAIOdCAHwAAEA%3d%3d&EntityRepresentationId=83d17adf-55a3-4430-8f32-24383a2ba709)  \n- **Time:** 4:05 PM – 5:00 PM  \n- **Organizer:** [Travis Wilson](https://www.office.com/search?q=Travis+Wilson&EntityRepresentationId=02246d9d-0f36-4b5c-a221-422944d3db4a)  \n- **Location:** Microsoft Teams + Focus Room 16/1M03 / Conf Room 16/11  \n- **Status:** Already ended  \n- **Notes:** Weekly recurring meeting with your manager and team context. 【1-23993e】  \n\n---\n\n#### 2. [AI Foundry SDK/API Reviews](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meeting/details?eventId=AAMkAGI4NTJlOTY2LWVhYTgtNDUwMy04MmFlLTBiOTFhY2EyYmI5NAFRAAgI3rq5ut3AAEYAAAAAxlcDfIcKC0iM2tlcAvavNgcAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QAAAAABDQAAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QADjeEUBgAAEA%3d%3d&EntityRepresentationId=37f91280-6281-40c1-9b67-1a561419e788)  \n- **Time:** 6:05 PM – 7:00 PM  \n- **Organizer:** [Dan Taylor](https://www.office.com/search?q=Dan+Taylor&EntityRepresentationId=c637600b-ecc3-4a74-b594-288dabe5cda3)  \n- **Location:** Microsoft Teams  \n- **Response:** Tentatively accepted  \n- **Notes:**  \n  - Large group meeting (50+ attendees)  \n  - Includes collaborators like [Darren Cohen](https://www.office.com/search?q=Darren+Cohen&EntityRepresentationId=756f1257-9e99-4012-8239-9f8f23426396) and [Sindhura Bandhakavi](https://www.office.com/search?q=Sindhura+Bandhakavi&EntityRepresentationId=41aa16e7-6792-411b-84a1-9a02beedc3b2)  \n  - ⚠️ **Conflicts with Team Lunch** 【2-324bb1】  \n\n---\n\n#### 3. [Team Lunch](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meeting/details?eventId=AAMkAGI4NTJlOTY2LWVhYTgtNDUwMy04MmFlLTBiOTFhY2EyYmI5NAFRAAgI3rq5ut3AAEYAAAAAxlcDfIcKC0iM2tlcAvavNgcAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QAAAAABDQAAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QADjeFGvwAAEA%3d%3d&EntityRepresentationId=168e2b3d-68c0-46dd-836e-7988dd984bd3)  \n- **Time:** 6:45 PM – 8:00 PM  \n- **Organizer:** [Travis Angevine](https://www.office.com/search?q=Travis+Angevine&EntityRepresentationId=ce5fc639-d8ed-4e3d-bf19-52a2c79c8406)  \n- **Location:** Building 16 Lobby  \n- **Notes:**  \n  - Includes many of your teammates (e.g., [Howie Leung](https://www.office.com/search?q=Howie+Leung&EntityRepresentationId=88bf20bb-8097-4175-922a-ebe070f7051b), [Kaylie Leung](https://www.office.com/search?q=Kaylie+Leung&EntityRepresentationId=35274a75-52a9-481f-a013-3146e795f024), [Sophia Ramsey](https://www.office.com/search?q=Sophia+Ramsey&EntityRepresentationId=6aacd3bb-d39e-4c95-b0a4-c33a4644ec3c))  \n  - ⚠️ Overlaps with the SDK/API Reviews meeting 【3-8f88a1】  \n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ Key Conflict to Be Aware Of\n- **6:05 PM – 7:00 PM:** [AI Foundry SDK/API Reviews](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meeting/details?eventId=AAMkAGI4NTJlOTY2LWVhYTgtNDUwMy04MmFlLTBiOTFhY2EyYmI5NAFRAAgI3rq5ut3AAEYAAAAAxlcDfIcKC0iM2tlcAvavNgcAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QAAAAABDQAAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QADjeEUBgAAEA%3d%3d&EntityRepresentationId=37f91280-6281-40c1-9b67-1a561419e788)  \n- **6:45 PM – 8:00 PM:** [Team Lunch](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meeting/details?eventId=AAMkAGI4NTJlOTY2LWVhYTgtNDUwMy04MmFlLTBiOTFhY2EyYmI5NAFRAAgI3rq5ut3AAEYAAAAAxlcDfIcKC0iM2tlcAvavNgcAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QAAAAABDQAAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QADjeFGvwAAEA%3d%3d&EntityRepresentationId=168e2b3d-68c0-46dd-836e-7988dd984bd3)  \n\nYou’re double-booked for ~15 minutes between **6:45–7:00 PM**, and realistically the overlap is larger if travel is involved.\n\n---\n\n### \uD83D\uDCA1 Quick Suggestions\n- Since you’ve **tentatively accepted** the SDK/API review, you may want to:\n  - Join the first part, then drop for the team lunch  \n  - Or fully commit to one depending on priority (technical vs team bonding)\n\n---\n\nIf you want, I can help you **resolve the conflict (e.g., decline/tentative one of them or find a better split)** or pull **agenda/details** for either meeting.\n","status":"completed"},"output_index":1,"sequence_number":6}

